Florida Senator  Bill Nelson  has
submitted legislation to allow hundreds of Holocaust survivors
to sue European insurance companies for millions of dollars in
unpaid claims, the Miami Herald reported, citing a statement by
Nelson released Wednesday.  Samuel Dubbin, an attorney for a South Florida survivorsâ€™
group, said experts have estimated that  Allianz SE (ALV) , Generali and
other insurers sold Eastern European Jews 879,000 life insurance
policies with a current value of about $18 billion, the
newspaper reported.  Read more:
